Assembler Instructions:

- Open an assembly (.asm) file and parse
- @ denotes an A-instruction, any following value is to be converted into binary and stored
- C-instructions are to be hard-coded
- Variables are to be stored in an address table starting from RAM register 16 and incremented
- Point markers i.e. (LOOP, RESET) are to be converted into A-instructions and assigned correct register
- // are to be ignored alongside contents that come after as these are code comments
- White space is to be ignored
- Create a text file under a file format of .hack containing parsed contents

