C-instruction Parser: 

Following this structure dest=comp;jump the C-instruction parser does the following actions:
    - Adds "j null" at the end of a string if no "j" is detected

    E.g. C-instruction: D = D + 1 ; JLE

    My approach is as follows: 
    - Anything before "=" is treated a dest variable
    - Anything between "=" & ";" is treated as computational variable
    - Anything after ";" is treated as a jump variable
